THB SPEAKER—It is a well understood rule that no amendment to a motion for an adjournment can be proposed, unless it relates to the time to which the adjournment is pro- posed to be made. The ﬁrst portion of the motion is in order, or would be in order if it were separated from what follows, and pro- posed by itself ; but I cannot compel the hon- orable mover of it to alter it. According to the best of my judgment, the motion is out of order.
